{
  "stem": "23410.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my father's family-- we were in the same town and-- and saw them very often.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was-- and also my brothers, sisters-- it was a normal relationship between young brothers and sisters.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I went to school, they went to school, and so on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But mostly, like at this time, girls were kept separate, and boys are separate.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I did not mean by separate, but it was no really interaction too much.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because since I was three, I was taken to a cheder, a Jewish school, and learned every day.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so it was different responsibilities.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we grew up of different philosophies and responsibilities for boys and girls.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Shabbat was the absolute holy day which-- that you did not do anything on this day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The boys-- women never went to the synagogue, like here or something, or [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so only the men went to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the father, with his boys, went to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In this way, I believe, kept us also separation between-- brothers and sisters-- at home, because we had different directions to go on, to do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were going to the synagogue every Friday night and Saturday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was our-- and afterwards, we had our lunch.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And afterwards, we had our rest of the day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the father, mother, and the children played outside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we all knew about the holy day of [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Shabbat. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a fairly stable, but a very unknown separation of-- of Jews and non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was separate living, separate background, separate responsibility for the future, separate ideas.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, I-- I was going to cheder.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never knew non-Jewish children before the war, when I was small.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I never played--",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
